						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Madanagōpāla svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>1713 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1635, Vijaya, Vaiśākha śu. 15 corresponding to April 29, Wednesday, 1713 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of silver and gold idols (<hi rend="italic">rajata</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kāṁchana vigrahamulu</hi>) of Madanagōpāla swami made by Timma-reḍḍi of Peddanapāḍu. He also set up the <hi rend="italic">dvajastaṁbha</hi> as well as <hi rend="italic">dīpastaṁbha</hi> in the temple complex and performed the <hi rend="italic">garuḍōtsava</hi> for the deity.</p>						

						</summary>
